arguments.prompt:
Create a complete Blazor Web App for building inspectors on construction sites in `/tmp/sv-9f3ddf909e894a778a38c99638d0986a/SiteInspector`.

## Architecture

- **Blazor WebAssembly PWA** (standalone, offline-first) — the client runs entirely in the browser
- **ASP.NET Core Web API** — server that hosts the WASM client and provides sync endpoints
- **Shared class library** — models shared between client and server
- .NET 10 (SDK 10.0.300 is installed)
- No authentication

## Solution Structure

```
SiteInspector/
├── SiteInspector.sln
├── src/
│   ├── SiteInspector.Client/       # Blazor WASM PWA
│   ├── SiteInspector.Server/       # ASP.NET Core Web API (hosts client + sync API)
│   └── SiteInspector.Shared/       # Shared models
```

## Step-by-step instructions

### 1. Scaffold projects

```bash
mkdir -p /tmp/sv-9f3ddf909e894a778a38c99638d0986a/SiteInspector/src
cd /tmp/sv-9f3ddf909e894a778a38c99638d0986a/SiteInspector

dotnet new sln -n SiteInspector
dotnet new blazorwasm -n SiteInspector.Client -o src/SiteInspector.Client --pwa
dotnet new webapi -n SiteInspector.Server -o src/SiteInspector.Server --no-openapi
dotnet new classlib -n SiteInspector.Shared -o src/SiteInspector.Shared

dotnet sln add src/SiteInspector.Client
dotnet sln add src/SiteInspector.Server
dotnet sln add src/SiteInspector.Shared

cd src/SiteInspector.Server
dotnet add reference ../SiteInspector.Shared
dotnet add reference ../SiteInspector.Client/SiteInspector.Client.csproj

cd ../SiteInspector.Client
dotnet add reference ../SiteInspector.Shared

cd ../SiteInspector.Server
dotnet add package Microsoft.AspNetCore.Components.WebAssembly.Server
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Sqlite
dotnet add package Microsoft.EntityFrameworkCore.Design
```

After scaffolding, remove the template default files that we won't use (like the weather forecast stuff).

